        dc:description           "Figures 172–180. Bactericera nigrilla, last instar. 172) Habitus. 173) Habitus, probably parasitized. 174) Habitus, cleared specimen. 175) Marginal sectasetae of head. 176) Marginal sectasetae of forewing pad. 177) Marginal sectasetae of hindwing pad. 178) Marginal sectasetae of caudal plate. 179) Circumanal rings. 180) Tarsal apex. Scales:74) 0.4 mm; 175–178) 0.04 mm; 179) 0.04 mm; 180) 0.02 mm. (Photos by Lyle Buss, University of Florida, Entomology Department: 172, 173)." ;
